captions.text:
-Weren't we gonna do something
on January 18th?

coming back from the break like
a boomerang made of boogers.

-Why? Why would anyone want
a boomerang made of boogers?

-Hey, can the questions, Pear.
Before we get in with the new,

let's get out with the old.
-(announcer) That's right.

"Hey Orange,
have you ever driven a car?"

how are you steering
when you don't have hands?

-(announcer) "Can you squirt
a pepper into Pear's eye?"

Aah, my eye! Ah, it burns!
[Orange laughs]

Whoa! Why would
you ask him to do that?

-He got carried away
by a big breeze. [laughs]

-Ze cheese, it is all mine.
[babbles incoherently]

What rhymes with life
and is the opposite of spoon?"

-What? How is a fife
opposite of a spoon?

-(announcer) "Orange,
what school do you go to?"

the Los Angeles University
of Annoying Arts.
Try saying that five times fast.
but I'll shave it for later."

-Wow, you sound like
a real shave driver. [laughs]

-(announcer)
"Can you do fus ro dah on Pear?"

[grunts]
Why are you doing this to me?!

-(announcer) "I look up to you.
Is that a bad thing?"

-Of course not. Midget Apple
looks up to me all the time.

Because he's so--
-Don't even say it!

-(announcer) "Can one of my
comments be on your show?"

-(announcer) "Hey Orange,
why do you laugh so much?"

why would anyone want
a boomerang made of boogers?"

-Don't ask me, Pearfan.
I don't nose. [laughs]

Yo, yo, yo,
my TV show is on the go.

My TV show is moving from
Mondays to Thursdays.

It all starts January 24th at
7:30 PM only on Cartoon Network.

[Irish accent]: Orange you glad
I told ya? [laughs]

Thursdays. 7:30.
Do it. Do it now!
